Have you read the proposal yet?  That's exactly how I wrote it up; the
"Moderator" is a player of one of the Member Nomics.  The turn period I
have in there is two weeks, but that is easily changed.

> the Secretary-General of the United Nations is not a nation, but a
> person.  the UN elects the Secretary-General at large; however, the UN
> is not a Game (or at least is a considerably different sort of game).

"Considerably different"?  Well, that's arguable.  But yes, the sec-gen
is just a great big Moderator/Speaker type.

> David> At this time, I do not envision our individual Players being
> David> bound by any inter-Nomic Rules; inter-nomic is just a Game
> David> played by all Agorans, collectively.
> 
> the only likely way an Agoran Player could be bound by InterNomic
> rules would be for that Player to accept an Official Post in
> InterNomic.

I haven't provided for Offices in Internomic, but I envision them
popping up fairly soon.  In any case, the Internomic could theoretically
require our Nomic to require the Players to do things, but if we really
didn't like it, we could just withdraw from the Internomic.

