Quoth Kelly:
> 
> i disagree.  i would prefer to see points used for exactly two
> purposes: to win the game, and to buy marks.  this way, the player
> must choose if e wants to win the game, or if e wants to utilize eir
> points into buying services and other such things by converting them
> to marks which are then usable for other things--but not for winning
> the game.

I agree completely.  However, the question is how penalties and bonuses
are awarded.  As a completely radical thought (which just occurred to me
as I was typing this message): Disallow Point transfers completely.
That would mean that each Player would win on the merit of eir own
accomplishments and no other, although business could still be
transacted.

After a little thought, here is a brief protoproto, which I may
formulate into something more formal if there is interest:

* Convert all non-Player Point holdings to Marks at the prevalent rate
  of transfer (presumably 25P:1M).
* Disallow all Point transfers.
* Keep all salaries as Point-based, as well as penalties; convert all
  "fees" (e.g. for multiple Proposals) to Marks
* Institute EOG point-Mark conversion at somewhat less than the
  prevalent conversion rate (say about 40P:1M)
* Modify FOIA to allow for Rules which require payments (in Marks) for
  certain documents.

Other possibilities which would not be immediately incorporated into the
initial Proposal: allow purchase of OoM-type abilities; Powers
(revised); Vototron; deposition from Office; anything else we haven't
already thought of...

> k.

Vanyel

