Here are the implementations I said I'd include: 

Implementation section, #1: FTF
301. The players of this nomic are xxxxx, yyyyy, zzzzzz, and wwwwww.
302. Play proceeds in turns; a player has a turn immediately after the
     player on eir left.  A player may only make a proposal when it is
     eir turn.  This takes precedence over a rule which would allow a
     player to make a proposal any other time.
303. The Voting Period begins immediately after the proposal is made,
     and lasts until every player has voted.
304. A player is within the scope of the rules until the game ends or e
     forfeits, whichever comes first.

Implementation section, #2: MUD (hey, I tried to pick two implementation
sections that'd be as different as possible! :)
301. A player is any person with an account on the mud.  They are within
     the scope of the rules whenever they are logged in to the mud.
302. All players may always use all non-Nomic related mud commands,
     including but not limited to movement and socials.
303. To submit a proposal, a player must use the proposal verb to enter
     the proposal.  The voting period commences immediately, and lasts
     one week.
304. To vote, a player must use the vote verb with the number of the
     proposal and eir vote.
305. Votes must be "F" or "A".
306. Proposals, proposal results, disputes, and judgements each have
     their own message board, which will be system-writable only.
307. To submit a dispute, a player must use the dispute verb to enter
     the text of the dispute.  A unique number will then be assigned to
     it.
308. To submit a judgement, a judge must use the judge verb with the
     number of the dispute, then enter the text of eir judgement.

An additional note: 101 would have to have "while they are within the
scope of the rules" appended to it, because of course the scopes are
different depending on the implementation.

Vanyel

-=-=-=-Don Blaheta-=-=-=-blahedo@quincy.edu-=-=-=-dblaheta@aol.com-=-=-=-

One thing the inventors can't seem to get the bugs out of is fresh
paint.

