(This is probably the form in which this will be proposed, if at all.
 The primary goal of increasing nomic activity seems to have been served 
 just by the threat of proposing this...  I'm still interested in what
 the voting patterns on all of this would be, and which ones would pass.)

 
PROTO: Repeals I (Contests...) 
Rules 1446 and 1515 are hereby Repealed.


PROTO: Repeals I.1 (... & Contracts)
Rules 1455, 1458, 1459, 1456, 1457 and 1499 are hereby Repealed.


{Justification: Contests and Contracts have been around long enough
 and have died out for lack of use.  Even the rabid proponents of
 Contracts haven't done anything to actually *use* the huge body
 of enabling legislation.  I've split the two up since there seems
 to be a dichotomy btween those who favor one over the other.
 1500 can be amended later, if it still exists.}


PROTO: Repeals II (The Assistant.)

Rule 839 is hereby Repealed.

{Justification: The Assistant (as in the Office of) is deadwood. Typo Fixed.}


PROTO: Repeals III (Degrees.)

Rules 1367, 1368, 1369, 1370, 1371, are hereby repealed.

{Justification: Essesntilally little used, but a large block of
 text nonetheless.  If a majority of Players vote for their repeal
 they should be repealed.)


PROTO:  Repeals IV (Protos.)

Rule 1443 is hereby repealed.

(Justification: is needless recordkeeping for only two points.)


PROTO:  Repeals V (Virus.)

Rule 1454 is hereby Repealed.
(Justification: The Virus has enough of a run in its current form.)


PROTO:  Repeals VI (Groups.)

Rules 766, 715, 717, 716, 719, 721, 1514, 1501, 1474, 1397, 1324
      1500 and 718 are hereby repealed.

{Justification: Now I don't expect this one to pass, really.  But
 it does force a referendum on the concept.  Perhaps you may 
 consider exactly *why* you're voting against this one?)


PROTO: Repeals VII (Titles #1.)

Rules 1008 and 1379 are herby Repealed
(Shogun, Honorless Worm, Samourai)


PROTO: Repeals VIII (Titles #2.)

Rule 840 is hereby Repealed
(Scamster)


PROTO: Repeals IX (Titles #3.)

Rule 1047 is hereby Repealed
(Zeitgeist)


PROTO: Repeals X (Titles #4.)

Rules 649, 1044, 755 and 51 are hereby repealed.
(Enabling legislation for titles, and the Champion & Hero title.)


PROTO: Repeals XI (Obey the Rules?)

Rule 101 is hereby Repealed.

(Justification:  None, but there's a continuing debate over the
 so-called redundancy of this Rule.  Are we willing to put it to
 the test?)

PROTO: Repeals XII (Ambassador.)

Rule 1070 and 893 are hereby repealed.




