vanyel, you've compelled me to at least try.

i am going to _attempt_ to work out a variation on my corporations
proto that will support contracts.  it will _also_ support parties.

i'm creating three distinct partitions of all corporations, along
three "axes":

Open vs. Closed:  Open Corporations have public Bylaws, and their
existence is generally known.  Closed Corporations have private
Bylaws, and their existence is generally secret.

Voluntary vs. Involuntary:  Players cannot be forced to join Voluntary
Corporations; they can be forced to join Involuntary Corporations.

Adhesive vs. Non-Adhesive:  Players cannot be made to stay in an
Non-Adhesive Corporation, but can be forced to stay in Adhesive ones.
the term comes from contract law: an "adhesion contract" persists, in
whole or in part, even after the contract has expired or been
terminated or breached.  i've also considered "sticky" and "slippery".

Groups and Contests are both Open, Voluntary, and Non-Adhesive.
Contracts would be Closed, Voluntary, and Adhesive.  Parties would be
Open, and Involuntary, and probably Adhesive (because there are limits
on when you can change Party).

i may find it necessary to create additional partitions, as i work
through the details.

k.
