i had this idea while semi-conscious this morning.

define agoraspace as an infinite plane (or maybe not so infinite, i
dunno).  probably a lattice is better than a continuous plane.

each player would occupy one lattice cell; more than one player in a
cell is ok.  

cells would have ownerships, and anything that can own currencies can
own cells.  entering an owned cell would require the permission of the
cell's owner (although forcible entry would be a possibility)

unowned cells can be claimed by moving to them and paying a (small)
finder's fee.

certain cells would have "resources" and the owner of such cells would
be able to exploit them in some way.  the exact nature of these
resources would need to be determined.  players could also build
improvements (consuming resources in the process) that would increase
the production of resources in that cell, or perhaps converting one
type of resource into another.

i had the strange idea of having Players emit "energy", and having the
right improvement within a certain radius of a Player would allow you
to collect this energy and convert it to something useful.

anyway, certain resources would yield Marks either directly or through
trade (actually i think Marks would be a resource, roughly equivalent
to gold or something similar).

i have also been meandering over the idea of allowing Players to
purchase Extra Votes with Marks.  my first idea was to have the cost
of the nth EV bought in a given week cost n squared Marks; obviously,
some sort of scaling may be needed to prevent this from becoming
unbalanced.  this would "close the loop", because points would lead to
marks which would lead to extra votes which can lead to points.

k.
