Jeff Caruso writes:
>
>Prospective Wanderlust contestants FYI:
>
>Here are the final regulations of the Wanderers contest which was
>dissolved in May 1995.
>

And here are some ideas I've been tossing around to elaborate the
oringinal Wanderer's concept:

* each move, Players may place a single barrier between two squares,
  which prevents movement between those two squares.
* begin with some barriers already on the board (a 'maze').
* allow Players to pay the CF to destroy barriers (increasing the prize pool)
* allow some games to have 'wrapped' boards, so that play takes places
  on a virtual cylinder (by joining just the vertical edges of the board),
  or on a virtual sphere (by joining both vertical and horizontal edges).
* play on a hex board, and vary the size of the board.
* have 'water' squares which cannot be moved onto, placed randomly.
* moves happen in batches, 3 turns per week, at 0000 GMT Tuesday, Thursday,
  Saturday. (This means you make one turn on Sat-Sun-Mon, one on Tue-Wed,
  and one on Thu-Fri).

Basically I envisage a set of variables with which the game can be configured
differently each round. Anyone ever played xbattle? Similar idea.

