Kelly responds to the COE:

> COE accepted.  an argument might be made that Rule 116 permits the
> transfer, but i doubt the prevailing attitude toward Rule 116 would
> support that argument.
> 
> a revised report will be published eventually.  i might also add that
> this COE was properly directed to the Banker, not the Scorekeepor, but
> since i'm the same person i'll not raise the issue that this COE is
> strictly meaningless because of the misdirection.

It was wrong in any case.  I was just about to get annoyed and go
through the Ruleset to refute the above, when I carefully reread the
rule defining Class II and III transfers... well, it turns out that the
1-Mark transfers were supposed to be Class III and not II, because of
the way I worded the Regulations.  *blush*  Sorry about that; I'm about
to propose to the Contestants that we fix that (well, once the whole
Organization thing clears up), but for now:  REPEAL BOOKIE CONTESTANTS,
PAY ATTENTION: You owe the Contest 6 Marks apiece.  (Except for
Morendil, who I have recorded as "might be a Contestant", not sure about
that.)

From the Repeal Bookie Compact (note the second part of this):
5. When a Rule is Repealed from Agora Nomic, the following shall occur:
   * If any Contestant bet on that Rule, half the treasury is divided
     evenly among all Contestants who bet on that Rule.  Each such
     Contestant must choose a new Rule to bet on.
   * Every Contestant must transfer 1 Mark to the Contest Treasury.

From 1472:
      A transfer which is not required to take place, and which is
      instead the consequence of a Player's action, is initiated by
      that Player, and is a called a Class III Transfer.

      For the purpose of this Rule, a Rule, or an Entity other than
      the Rules to which the Rules have granted the power to require
      Players to perform actions, which requires a Player to initiate
      a transfer is _not_ requiring the transfer.  Such a transfer is
      a Class III transfer initiated by that Player.  This Rule takes
      precedence over any Rule which would require a Player to
      initiate a transfer which is prohibited by this Rule.

In retrospect (hindsight is 20/20!) I should have worded that "One
Mark is transferred from every Contestant to the Contest Treasury".
*sigh*

> k.

Vanyel

