From: jlc@triple-i.com (Jeff Caruso)
Message-Id: <9511061717.AA05205@zeus.Camex.COM>
To: nomic-business@teleport.com
Subject: BUS: Proto-Proposal
Sender: owner-nomic-business@teleport.com
Precedence: bulk
Reply-To: nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Status: RO

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Proto-Proposal (MI=1)
Philanthropic Gestures

Create a rule which reads:

   A Proposal is defined to be a Philanthropic Gesture if it is so 
   designated by its Proposer when it is submitted to the Promotor.

   Any score or currency changes regarding formatting penalties, 
   rule repeal rewards, new player bonuses, and awards or penalties 
   for votes cast for such a Proposal are cancelled and shall not be 
   taken into account.  The Proposer does not receive any Extra Votes 
   for a Proposal so designated, even if it passes. 

   This Rule takes precedence over any other Rule which would
   otherwise seek to reward or penalize any player based on the
   designated proposal. 

-------------------------------------------------------------------
Reasons:

They had something like this in Thring, I think.  The idea is to 
allow Proposals to make obvious fixes like typos, without Players 
needing to worry about whether the Proposer will get a big F-A Point 
windfall for a trivial Proposal.  I'd probably vote FOR more of these
"typo" proposals if they could be so designated.

The language is lifted from the "Disowning" rule, except that it allows
the Proposal to pass if it gets enough votes, and does not cost 5 points.
Also the designation must be made when the thing is submitted, not later.

Regards,
- elJefe

******************************************************************
  Dr. Jeffrey L. Caruso <jlc@triple-i.com>
  Information International

