> obvious apologetic directions; has it ever actually been used
> for that?  *8)

I don't remember it ever being used that way!    :-)

> I admit that the current "punishment by
> creativity" policy is much more fun...

You should have _seen_ some of the word lists of the past!  

Oh, Archivist Vanyel, can you dig out some of the juicer Public Apologies
and post them?    

