Champion Champion Wes, said Patent Titles having been awarded on Friday,
October 29, 1993 with the passage of Proposal 654 in reward for Winning
the First and Fourth Games of eNomic. 

In the spirit of cooperation, we would like to contribute to the
well-being of Nomic, and so would like to contribute to the Agora
community by holding one of our old Offices, probably either the
Rulekeepor or Registrar, since we are not yet familiar enough with the
new Rule Set to successfully hold the Office of Scorekeepor. If the
holder of either of these two Offices could see eir way to ceed us one
of these Offices, perhaps leaving them with enough time to manage
Scorekeeping, please indicate so to us. 


We are also making a few official requests for information maintained by
an Officer as per Rule 1064. 

  -- We would like to request from the Archivist the records of Proposals 
     773 through the present and all CFJ's to date. 
  -- We would like to request from the Rulekeepor the Numerical Rule Set.
  -- We would like to request from the Promotor a copy of all Proposals
     currently up for Vote. 
  -- We would like to request from the Clerk of the Courts a copy of all
     Calls for Judgements or Appeals currenty being decided. 


Lastly, we would like to invite any Players who wish to cooperate with
us in streamlining the Rule Set or in fixing the lack of definition in
the current Compact/Organization Rules to let us know so that we may
discuss how to proceed on these projects. Also, if anyone would be
agreeable to a temporary suspension of the limits to multiple Proposals,
this process would be considerably easier, faster, and more controllable
by the majority. 

Thank you. 


Enjoy!

---
Champion Champion Wes                                 
magika@teleport.com                             http//www.teleport.com/~magika   

