> > If the Honorary Officer concept is successful, I intend to Propose
> > that a Proposal author may act as Honorary Promotor, and distribute 
> > eir own Proposals in the Official part of the PF.
> 
> But e may not assign that Proposal a Number. Please keep that within the
> bounds of the actual Office; otherwise we have mass confusion. 

I agree. How about the following :

a) Non-protoed Proposals are submitted in the traditional manner.
b) When a Proto is submitted, the Promotor replies with a Proposal 
Number. A Proposer may then distribute that Proposal (three to 
fourteen days afterward) with the assigned Number, acting as Honorary 
Promotor.

This would require an amendment to the Proposal Numbering Rule, of 
course. Is there a way to do something like this without amending 
that Rule, and still let a Proposer distribute eir own Proposals 
without significant delay ?

