From: "Laurent Bossavit" <morendil@micronet.fr>
To: nomic-business@teleport.com
Date:          Sat, 11 Nov 1995 01:17:47 +0001
Subject: BUS: PROTO : Classes of Moves
Priority: normal
X-mailer: Pegasus Mail for Windows (v2.0-WB3)
Sender: owner-nomic-business@teleport.com
Precedence: bulk
Reply-To: nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Status: RO

Proto-proposal
---
Classes of Moves

Create a Rule with this text (Classes of Moves) :

   A Move is defined as any action taken by a Player, or Entity acting 
   as a Player, that affects the Game State. This Rule defines when 
   and under what conditions a Move in general takes effect, and as 
   such takes precedence over all other Rules.

   There are three classes of Moves.

   Class I Moves take effect immediately, at the time date-stamped
   on the message these Moves are the result of, or at the time 
   specified for these Moves to take effect by the Rules if the Rules 
   do so specify. These Moves shall only be retracted if an Injuction 
   to that effect is issued.

   Class II Moves take effect at the time specified for them to take 
   effect in the Rules, or no later than any subsequent Moves made if 
   the Rules do not so specify. If a CFJ alleging that a Class II 
   Move is illegal is submitted within 48 hours of that Move or that 
   Move's effect (whichever is sooner) being published to the Public 
   Forum, that Move is immediately retracted until the CFJ is Judged. 
   That Move will only take effect if the CFJ is Judged FALSE, and 
   then take effect at the time the Judgement is distributed by the 
   CotC. If that Judgement is Appealed, the Move is again retracted 
   and only takes effect if the Final Judgement is FALSE, at the time 
   the Final Judgment is distributed.

   Class III Moves take effect immediately, at the time date-stamped
   on the message these Moves are the result of, or at the time 
   specified for these Moves to take effect by the Rules if the Rules 
   do so specify. Any Officer to whom a Rule specifically grants 
   authority to retract a particular Move of Class III may do so at 
   eir sole discretion, but must at the same time delegate all futher 
   duties to a willing Player until a CFJ has determined the legality 
   of the Move.

   A Rule defining how a Move is made may in addition specify
   the Class of that Move. Any Move is a Class II Move unless
   defined by exactly one Rule to be of Class I, II or III.
---

Comments : prompted by Vanyel's notes, the Mousetrap Scam,
and my own reflexions on how Agora should handle Moves and
political power in general.

With this, anything that is too problematic can be prevented from 
having effect immediately, while ensuring (after we start adding Move 
Class specs to critical Rules) that important Moves are protected 
from political meddling.

I suggest that the very first Rule to specify a Class III Moves 
should be the Rule specifying how a CFJ is submitted, so that the 
CotC can retract frivolous CFJs made only to block legitimate Class 
II Moves.

Revision history :
1 - Nov. 10, original proto

