KUNNE> The submission of a Proposal does not change the Game State.

hm.  i don't agree with this.  if the submission of a Proposal does
not change the Game State, then the submission of a Proposal has no
significance under the Rules.  but this is clearly not true, so it
_must_ change the Game State.  in fact, the submission of a Proposal
changes the Game State from one state in which the Promotor has no
obligation to distribute that Proposal, to another state in which the
Promotor is.

i think the problem here is not fully recognizing just what is in the
Game State.

