Ahem! "Celtic" is not "Germanic". As far as I know, they are not even 
closest relatives.

Celtic languages: Welsh, Irish, Scots Gaelic, extinct languages of Gaul

Germanic languages:
  East Germanic: Gothic (extinct)
  West Germanic: German, Dutch, English, Frisian
  North Germanic: Old Norse, Icelandic, Scandinavian languages

(I didn't include everything.)

