Proto-proposal
(Was : Classes of Moves)
---
Moves and Events

Create a Rule with this text (Definition of Moves and Events) :

   An Event is a modification to the Game State. All Events occur at 
   a definite time and take effect instantly at that time. Even if two 
   Events occur at the same time, they take effect one after the 
   other.

   A Move is part or all of an email message. Events occur either as 
   a direct result of the application of one or more Rules, or as a 
   result of one or more Moves.

   An Event that occurs as a result of a Move can occur before, 
   after, or at the time that Move is made.

   Only Moves made by Players are legal, unless a Rule specifically
   describes a case where a non-Player may make a legal Move.

Create a Rule with this text (Principles of Evidence)

   In all cases where a Player must determine whether an Event 
   occurred, only specific Moves or specific Rules shall be cited as
   evidence. This includes, but is not limited to, Calls for 
   Judgement and Official Duties.

   In all cases where there is an uncertainty as to the exact timing 
   of a Move, the following can be cited as evidence, each item in 
   this list taking precedence over the next unless other evidence is 
   supplied that puts its validity in doubt :
    - the time date-stamped on the message itself
    - the time appearing in any Received: header
    - the time when the message was received by the Player citing it 
      as evidence.

Create a Rule with this text (Types of Events)

   There are two types of Events : regulated and unregulated. A 
   regulated Event is one that the Rules only allow to occur as a 
   result of a Move in a particular form. All other Events are 
   unregulated.

   A Move can cause a regulated Event to occur only if it conforms to 
   the specifications of the Rules regulating that Event.
---

Comments : I have for the time being put aside concerns of when an 
Event caused by a Move occurs. There are, as Kelly pointed out, a lot 
of problems with that, and I'd like to know first if the above seems 
valid as groundwork for such legislation.

All three Rules are mainly of the Definition type, but all also 
introduce important principles : ordering of events, rules of 
evidence, grounds for summarily dismissing illegal Moves.

Revision history :
1 - Nov. 10, original proto
2 - Nov. 12
Introduced Events.
Introduced mail messages as the carrier of Moves.
This proto now owes a lot to Kelly. :)

