Don Blaheta writes:
>
>Rule 494, "Speaker Makes Random Determinations".  I am in favor of the
>Repeal of this Rule; it is unnecessary, especially with 1079.
>
>-----
>Proto Green-15
>Repeal Speaker-Randomness
>
>Whereas the Speaker no longer should have to do random calculations,
>
>Be it therefore resolved that Rule 1079 be Repealed.

You mean, of course, Rule 494, not Rule 1079. In any case, I disagree
with you that that 1079 makes 494 unnecessary; they do different things.
1079 defines randomness - that is one thing. 494 says the Speaker
makes random determinations if the Rules assign noone else to do so.
That is quite a different thing, and a very sensible safeguard into
the bargain.

I am against repealing Rule 494.

