Don Blaheta writes:
>-----
>Proto Green-18
>Axe the forbidden word in Rule 1043
>
>Whereas the word "may" has been found to have ambiguous meaning,
>
>Be it therefore resolved that Rule 1043 be Amended to read as follows:
>
>      A Voter is deregistered when, if, and only if e sends a message to
>      the Public Forum announcing eir Deregistration.  A Voter who
>      Deregisters in this fashion ceases to be a Player effective at the
>      time date-stamped on that message.  E may not re-Register as a
>      Player until a new Game has begun.
>-----

Two points: if "may" is such a terrible word, why have you left it
in the last sentence? Second, you have to watch this "when, if and
only if" stuff. It's simply not true that a Player is deregistered
*only if* they send a message to the PF. They can be deregistered
due to inactivity, for instance. In the future, deregistration might
be considered as a penalty.

