Vanyel writes:
>
>There might not be any explicit "Let there be an Office known as
>Banker....", but I see the extensive references to the Banker in the
>Ruleset to be enough to "specify" the Office.
>
Specify, yes, but no Rule saying the Banker is an Officer.
Hence, no way to replace eim, no reason why the Speaker should du
the Banker's work.
>
>First of all, even if "the Banker" weren't an Office, "the Banker" may
>be a Recordkeepor (as RKs needn't be Officers), so that's ok.  And in
>any case, the fact that the Banker is required to post "an Official
>Report to the Public Forum" is, to me, enough to imply that the Banker
>is an Officer.

I doubt it...
A message to the PF announcing the transfer of a currency to
another Player, or any Official Message of the Speaker (like:
I transfered all my files to the Elect) is an Official document too.

But it doesn't necessarily promote that Player or the Speaker to
Officer.

Ronald

