Reply-To: nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Status: RO


This event soes show one thing: We can have
a productive currency that is at the same
time non-existent (as far as the Rules are
concerned) *as long as we don't know that*
Now can we have such a currency if we do?
I propose we keep things as they are, and
not fix the banker thing.
  After all, 116 allows us to transfer these
virtual Marks, etc. The various Marks
penalties, etc. can also be paid (since
if the Rules demand virtual currency, virtual currency must be paid).
 As for a "recordkeepor", we could, by consensus, parallel
the system used by other, real, Offices.
The only problem is how to prevent wholesale
creation of virtual Marks. With regard to
transfers between Players, that is no problem:
don't trade with Players who do so. When dealing
with the Game (i.e. buying Powers), we have a
bit of a problem. Could we ignore player-generated
Marks by interpreting the Rules only to refer to
Game-generated Marks (since that is Game custom)?
I'd be interested to hear any other ideas.

Vlad

