> 
> Rule 795, "Accurate Quoting Shall Not Be Penalized".  I am indifferent
> to the Repeal of this Rule, since I agree with the principle behind
> it, yet in over a year of playing Agora, not once has it come into
> play.  I think we can safely Repeal it to shorten the Ruleset.

It was originally conceived when, during the FUN period of Nomic (when
PROSIRUP reigned (the PRoposers Of SIlly RUles Party) and we had a Rule
which specified how one must address the Speaker. First came: 

342.  Showing proper respect for the Speaker
      All future references to the Speaker shall refer to the Speaker as
      the "Mighty Speaker", the "Benevolent Speaker", or as the
      "Benevolent Mighty Speaker". Any Player who refers to the Mighty
      Speaker without using these respectful terms shall lose 5 Points
      per reference to the Benevolent Speaker which does not use these
      terms. Other terms may be approved by future legislation. The
      Benevolent, Mighty Speaker is not bound by this Rule. 

It was then Amended to read: 

357.  Respect for the Speaker
      When a Voter refers to the Nomic Speaker, or any other Speaker,
      that Voter must use one of the following adjectives in conjunction
      with the Speaker:

      Admirable, Amazing, August, Atonishing, Astounding, Beloved,
      Benevolent, Brilliant, Celebrated, Circumcised, Circumspect,
      Cogetive, Competant, Consummate, Courteous, Deserving, Devoted,
      Diligent, Distinguished, Divine, Effulgent, Elevated, Eminent,
      Excellent, Exceptional, Extraordinary, Exalted, Fabulous, Famed,
      Fine, Foremost, Generous, Glorious, Gracious, Grand, Great,
      Hallowed, High, Holy, Honored, Illustrious, Impartial, Impressive,
      Incredible, Industrious, Influential, Judicious, Just, Kind,
      Kosher, Kindred, Lofty, Magnificent, Majestic, Magnanimous,
      Marvelous, Mighty, Neat, Noble, Omnilaborant, Outstanding,
      Overworked, Persuasive, Pensive, Phenominal, Pious, Prime,
      Qualified, Quintessential, Regal, Reknown, Remarkable, Respected,
      Revered, Solicitous, Spectacular, Splendid, Superb, Superior,
      Transcendant, Trustful, Unparalleled, Upright, Unusual, Venerated,
      Vigilant, Virile, Virtuous, Watchful, Wonderful, Worshipped,
      Xenophilic, Zelous, or any combination of the preceeding. 

      Any Voter not following this directive shall lose 1 Point per
      reference to the Great and Virtuous Speaker which does not use one
      of the above words. 

The Rule you are referring to was intended to allow Players to provide
Proof of another's wrong-doing in reference to this Rule without being
Guilty of breaking the Rule eirself. <grin>  Currently, it would also
apply to the incorrect use of Patent Titles. 

And a bit of trivia, the next Rule assessed a penalty to anyone
submitting a Proposal with a word which beginned with "Y" because we
couldn't think of a Y-word to describe the Regal, Omnilaborous Speaker
and we were feeling snippy. <grin> Of course, it even said it would
Repeal itself if the Rule quoted above was Amended to include a
Y-Word... <grin>  

We do miss the good 'ole days when the object was to have fun, be a bit
silly, and pass interesting Rules, rather than concentrating on being
democratic and fair to all and trying to form the perfect society.
Remember, folks, Nomic is just a Game. 



For the most part, the rest of your commentary is fairly interesting,
and hopefully many of your Protos will make it to the Proposal stage.
Lots of little nitpicks that need to be done eventually. And lots of
Points to be gained by doing them.... <wink> 


Enjoy!

---
Wes Contreras      "Nonsense. You're only saying that because no one ever has."
