> 
> > > a Move is any action taken by a _person_ (not necessarily a Player,
> > > for a very important reason that will become apparent shortly) which
> > > causes one or more Events (which may occur before, at the same time
> > > as, or after the Move).  
> > 
> > We would submit that even non-person Entities may make some action which
> > must be contrued as a Move, such as Group Votes. Persons are Entities,
> > although they are not Game Entities as they have an existance outside
> > the Game. 
> 
> I disagree.  A Group Vote is an Automatic Event which occurs as a result
> of certain Manual Events...

So you are defining a Move solely as an action undertaken by a person?
Thus any result of that Move would be an Event. May we suggest a
modification? 

If we define a Move as any action undertaken by a Game Entity, that
would prevent a considerable but of trouble with regards to Groups.
Wouldn't it be MUCH easier to retract the Events resulting from a
Group's action than to try and negate the existance of a Group's action?
Also, it would be quite simple to define a person's Registration as a 
Player as an Event triggered by an action which is not necessarily a
Move. 

> > That would be one theory, but we would prefer to think of Players as a
> > sub-set of persons who have the ability to cause certain Events within
> > the Game. A Player is not a Game Entity, per se, since a Player will
> > exist outside the Game. However, the status of a Player is a Game
> > Entity, since that status has meaning only within Nomic. A person is
> > determined to be a Player when that person is Registered as described in
> > the Rules. 
> 
> This is somewhat contrary to the prevailing theory...  as I recall, the
> recent consensus was that the Player was the Agoran Entity, and the
> person the RL entity, and the Rules described a direct mapping of one to
> the other.  This is why a Player can remain contiguous through
> dereregistration cycles.

In what quasi-official capacity was this concensus made? For informative
purposes only, lest any vehement personage out there take offense...
<sigh> 


