actually, the US can still pay its debts (for a little while) by
tapping some cash-heavy trust funds.  all that lapsed today was the
authority to spend money.  tomorrow the authority to borrow money
lapses, which will force the Treasury to tap things like these trust
funds to continue to make payments on the national debt.  they can
probably do so for quite a while, although eventually payment would
have to be made in gold (once the aforementioned cash runs out).

