not force a national default.  it bothered me that congress did _not_
burn the midnight oil last night trying to reach a compromise; at 11PM
EST C-Span was showing four republicans "debating" before an empty
chamber about what a twit the president is.  i've seen the indiana
legislature stay in continuous session for weeks at a time (it's funny
to see legislators sleeping in the chambers) trying to reach budgetary
compromises; why can't Congress do the same thing?  then again, the
congresscritters are currently not being paid; their salaries are part
of the "nonessential" portion of the budget (so is the president's).

k.
