Oops, sent the wrong file!  *blush*

Here's the second installment... somewhat shorter although it covers
more Rules.  No CFJs, but there are 9 Protoes here.  For anyone keeping
count: I'm halfway through page 5... this covers three pages of my
ten-page printout...

*** CONTINUED FROM PART 1 ***

Rule 1339, "Rule Changes".  I'm against Repeal of this one; it
distinguishes types of Rule Change.


Rule 594, "Proposals and Rule Changes".  I'm against repeal.
Rulekeepor: 594/0 was enacted by Proposal 594 on 21 Oct 94.

Rule 993, "Directives".  I'm against repeal.
-----
Proto Green-27
Let the first lines make sense

Whereas "one or more" is a misleading method of stating permission,

Be it therefore resolved that Rules 594 and 993 be Amended by
replacing the words "one or more" with "zero or more".

Be it further resolved that Rule 993 be Amended by replacing the words
"be placed in a Proposal" in the first paragraph with "take effect".
-----
Rulekeepor: This rule was probably originally created by Proposal 807,
and later amended by Proposal 891 and finally by 993 (which was
distributed 11 Aug 94).


Rule 404, "Legality of Proposals".  I am indifferent to the fate of
this Rule, as it is redundant with Rule 116.  Rulekeepor: This rule
was enacted on 3 Sep 93 (our oldest non-original non-amended rule, I
think).


Rule 1036, "Making and Distributing Proposals".  I am against the
Repeal of this Rule, but perhaps it should be reTitled?  After all, it
is the rule which defines the Office of Promotor...  Rulekeepor: This
rule derives from the original Rule 204, which was amended by Proposal
415 on 3 Sep 93, and 1036 on 21 Sep 94.


Rule 1061, "Bonus to New Players".  I suppose this Rule serves a
purpose, but administratively speaking it's kind of annoying.  So I'm
FOR it's Repeal.  Rulekeepor: Proposal 1061 enacted this rule on 20Sep
94.


Rule 109, "Proposal Numbers".  I'm against the repeal of this Rule,
although I wouldn't oppose modifications to it similar to what has
been recently discussed... (I especially liked the idea of keeping the
Promotor, but for every Protoed Rule, a Proposal number would be
assigned.)


Rule 1349, "Rule Numbering".  I'm against the repeal of this Rule.
-----
Proto Green-28
Lose the bootstraps already

Be it resolved that Rule 1349 be Amended by deleting the text ", or
301, whichever is greater".
-----


Rule 659, "Rewards/Penalties Based on Length/Form of Proposal".  Is it
just me, or is this Rule a real pain?
-----
Proto Green-29
What a pain, lose the width-length penalty

Whereas Rule 659 only serves to annoy people who try to make omnibus
reform,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 659 be Repealed.
-----
Rulekeepor: Originally created by proposal 394 on 23 Aug 93, this rule
was later amended by Proposal 659 on 29 Oct 93.


Rule 748, "Blank/Required Lines Don't Count".  Is this really
necessary?  I'm indifferent to its Repeal.  Rulekeepor: This rule was
enacted on 1 Dec 93.


Rule 783, "Illegality of Bonus Clauses".  I'm against the Repeal of
this Rule, as for some reason group psychology is such that these
things actually _pass_.  Rulekeepor: Rule 326 was enacted on 19 Jul
93, and later amended by Proposal 783 sometime in January of 94.

Rule 1003, "No Coercive Proposals".  I'm against the Repeal of this
Rule, too, since people actually vote for these things half the time.
Should Rules 783 and 1003 be combined?  Obviously their content is
very similar; I'm not sure if it is different enough to warrant two
Rules.  Rulekeepor: This rule was probably created by Proposal 822,
between 14 and 22 Feb 94.  It was later amended by 1003 (which wwas
distributed 18 Aug 94).


Rule 1065, "Discourages Too Many Proposals".  I'm for the Repeal of
this Rule... it just gets in people's way.  Why would we want to
discourage too many Proposals?  Rulekeepor: Rule 843 was enacted on 3
Mar 94, amended by 936 (dist. 3 Jul 94), and then 1065 (dist. 4 Oct
94).



Category: Voting on Proposals


Rule 1449, "The Assessor".  Short and to the point, I'm against repeal
of this Rule.


Rule 106, "Adopting Proposals".  Against repeal.


Rule 693, "Prescribed Voting Period".  Against repeal.


Rule 1451, "Disowning Proposals".  I can't imagine why I ever liked
this idea... it's really annoying, though.  Especially in light of the
fact that Powers and EVs may or may not remain cast on a disowned
Proposal.  I'm FOR its Repeal.


Rule 206, "Voting Entities and Votes".  Against repeal.


Rule 452, "No Electioneering by Assessor".  Against repeal.
Rulekeepor: Rule 452/0 was enacted on 10 Sep 93.


Rule 683, "Legal Votes".  Against repeal.  Rulekeepor: Original Rule
207 was amended into Rule 683/0 on 10 nov 93.


Rule 957, "YES=FOR, NO=AGAINST, Anything else=ABSTAIN".  This is
redundant with 754, so I'm FOR its repeal.  Rulekeepor: 462 was
created 17 Sep 93, amended by 957 on 25 Jul 94.


Rule 312, "A Point for Voting".  Against repeal, at least until
Parties get into the picture (what's up with them?)  Rulekeepor: 312/0
was enacted 15 Jul 93.



Category: The End of the Voting Period


Rule 879, "Quorum".  Hm, is this necessary?  I'm indifferent here.
Rulekeepor: Proposal 879 Amended 201 on 13 Apr 94.


Rules 208, 955, 1322, 108, 376, and 1069 are too vital to be mucking
around with.  Against repeal.  Rulekeepor: 209 -> 396 (23 Aug 93) ->
658 (29 Oct 93) -> 761 (8 Dec 93) -> 955 (25 Jul 94);  210 -> 376 (16
Aug 93);  750 (1 Dec 93) -> 1069 (4 Oct 94).


Rule 1443, "Bonus for Proto-Proposing".  While not strictly necessary,
this is nice--it tends to cut down on making not-well-thought-out
Proposals.  Plus, if we ever tie Proposal Numbering to Proto-proposing
(even a little bit) this would be very easy to track.  Against repeal.


Rule 833, "Reward or Penalty for Proposing".  F-A is getting boring...
how about something new?
-----
Proto Green-30
New Reward/Penalty system

Whereas the F-A reward is getting boring,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 833 be Amended to read as follows:

      At the end of the Voting Period, the Proposal Reward for a given
      Proposal is calculated to be the greatest integer less than or
      equal to the number of FOR votes cast, squared, minus the number
      of AGAINST votes cast, squared, all over 10.  In mathematical
      notation, that is

                              |   2    2  |
                              |  F  - A   |
                              | --------- |
                              |_   10    _|

      If the Proposal Reward is positive, then the Proposor of that
      Proposal gains a number of Points equal to the Proposal Reward; if
      the Proposal Reward is negative, then the Proposor loses a number
      of Points equal to the absolute value of the Proposal Reward.
-----
Should be interesting, at least. Rulekeepor: Proposal 833 Amended Rule
544 on 1 Mar.  I haven't the faintest idea what Proposal 544 did.


Rule 1519, "Bonus for Short Proposals".  Again, this isn't
particularly necessary--I would much rather have short Rules than
short Proposals.  I'm FOR this repeal.


Rule 947, "Bonus for Repeal".  Why do we need this?  Especially after
the Green Repeals, the Ruleset should be about as pruned as necessary
for a while.  For repeal.  Rulekeepor: This rule was enacted by
Proposal 947, which was distributed 3 Jul 94.



Category: Referenda and Elections


Rule 1434, "Default Procedure for Referendum Voting".  Against repeal;
I think we can and should use this for Officer elections, at least.


Rule 1445, "Defaults for Elections".  Likewise, I'm against repeal.



Category: The Clerk of the Courts


Rule 889, "Clerk of the Courts", and 1450, "Speaker Cannot Stay CotC
or Justiciar", are important and shouldn't be repealed.  Rulekeepor:
This rule was enacted by Prop 406 on 3 Sep 94, and amended by Prop 889
on 13 Apr 94.


Rule 1484, "Separation of Powers".  This rule is unnecessary, I
think... I'm for repeal of it.



Category: Calling for Judgement
Obviously, we want to be _verrrry_ careful with these.  I'm against
repeal on all of these, but I have protoes for some... Kelly, let me
know if I'm stepping on your toes here, or whether you've given up on
Judicial reform.


Rule 991, "Invoking Judgement".
-----
Proto Green-31
Get rid of that "disagreement" junk

Whereas the first paragraph of Rule 991 is superfluous, and

Whereas we do not wish to have unnecessary uses of ambiguous "may"
language,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 991 be Amended by replacing the
first two sentences with the following text:

      A Call for Judgement is made when, if, and only if a Player sends
      a Statement for Judgement to the Clerk of the Courts.

and by removing the text "(*Was 407*)" and "This Rule defers to all
other Rules which do not contain this sentence."
-----

Rules 662 and 897 are ok (well, kind of--I'll let Kelly handle most of
that)

Rulekeepor: 213 -> 407 (3 Sep 93) -> 991 (dist. 5 Aug 94);  ?585? ->
662 (2 Nov 93);  897 (Apr 94).



Category: Selecting a Judge
All the Rules in this Category (951, 1005, 698) are fine.  Rulekeepor:
I do believe 951 is our Most Amended rule; it has 14 Amendments to it.
214 -> 364 (8 Aug 93) -> 410 (26 Aug 93) ?->? 586 (?) -> 647 (29 Oct
93) -> 793 (dist. 24 Jan 94) -> 890 (13 Apr 94) -> 951 (25 Jul 94).
Also 503 (30 Sep 93) -> 1005 (dist. 18 Aug 94); 482 (30 Sep 93) ->
6948 (12 Nov 93).



Category: Delivering Judgement
All the Rules in this Category (48, 591, 217, 451, 502, 663, 665, 289,
1500, 1365) are ok and I'm afraid to mess with them. :)
Rulekeepor stuff: 215 -> 408 (3 Sep 93);  216 -> 409 (26 Aug 93) ->
591 (21 Oct 93);  451 (10 Sep 93);  430 (dist 6 Sep 93) -> 502 (30 Sep
93);  663 (2 Nov 93);  665 (2 Nov 93);  789 (dist. 7 Jan 94).


Category: Overturning Judgement
All the Rules in this Category (911--do you realize how appropriately
this rule is numbered?!--, 910, 1448, 1447) are ok and needn't be
messed with at this time.  Rulekeepor's mess: 384 (dist. 16 Aug 93) ->
690 (11 Nov 93) -> 911 (4 May 94); 910 (4 May 94).



Category: Rule Violations


Rule 908, "Formal Apologies".  This Rule is far too cute and amusing
(punishment by creativity, indeed) to repeal. :)  Rulekeepor: Proposal
781 was distribute 13 Dec 93, and enacted, and later amended by 908 on
4 May 94.



Category: Crimes and Infractions
The Rules in this Category, while not inviolable, are sturdy and seem
to hold up nicely.  As I like the pragmatic content, I am against
repeal.



Category: The Distributor and the Assistant


Rule 796, "The Distributor".  Against Repeal.
-----
Proto Green-33
Modernize the Distributor

Whereas official business now occurs over the Public Forum,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 796 be Amended to read as follows:

      There is an Office called the Office of Distributor.  The
      Distributor is in charge of the Public Forum, and the distribution
      of Official documents to all Players.  The Salary of the
      Distributor is 2 Points.
-----
Rulekeepor: The Distributor came into being as Rule 510 on 5 Oct 93,
and was later amended by 796 (dist. 24 Jan 94).


Rule 514, "Keep the Distributor Informed of Your Address".  I am FOR the
Repeal of this Rule, as the Registrar already keeps this information.
(Furthermore, the restriction is trivially fulfilled by the Player's
address appearing in a Registrar's Report.)  Rulekeepor: Enacted in
current form 5 Oct 93.


Rule 512, "Distributor Tries Three Times Then Quits".  Against repeal.
-----
Proto Green-34
Clarify 512

Be it resolved that Rule 512 be Amended by replacing "the Distributor"
in the first sentence with "official mail", and by inserting "by the
Distributor" between "shall be made" and "to contact".
-----
Rulekeepor: Enacted in current form 5 Oct 93.


Rule 513, "Distributor Golds On to Messages".  Against repeal.
-----
Proto Green-35
Distributor isn't forwarding anymore

Whereas the Distributor no longer directly forwards official mail to
Players,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 513 be Amended by replacing "he
forwards to all Players" with "are sent to the Public Forum".
-----
Rulekeepor: Enacted in current form 5 Oct 93.


Rule 839, "Office of the Assistant".  My Proposal 1791 already covers
this.  Rulekeepor: The Assistant was created by Prop 839 on 1 Mar 94.

*** CONTINUED ***

