Vanyel:

> Exactly correct on all counts.  This project has, however, been shoved
> to the back-burner for the past few months as more pressing concerns
> reared their ugly heads.

OK, I'll jump in some!  Here's how I picture the Platonization
Project going:

  - Define some infrastructure to take the place of current
    Rule Violations:
    - Define four new Classes of Crime (probably 1, 2, 3, and 4?),
      to correspond to violating MI=N Rules; penalties are N Blots
      for each.
    - Update 908 (Formal Apologies), expanding it to cover Crimes
      as well as Rule Violations,
    - Update 662 to allow for a CFJ to the effect that a Player
      has committed a specific Crime (if necessary),
    - No doubt some other stuff.

  - Systematically find those Rules that admit of being broken,
    and change (for instance) "No Player shall X" to "A Player
    who Xs commits a Class 1 Crime".

  - Fix up the Compact Rules along the same lines: require that
    Compacts be Platonic, and allow them to specify that certain
    actions by Players under their Jurisdiction are Crimes of a
    certain Class.

  - Get rid of some Rules that are no longer needed at all,
    such as 1439 (unless a Criminalized version is needed),
    and the Rule-violation wording in 908.

  - Fix 101 to require explicitly say that the Rules are Platonic,
    and perhaps that non-Platonist Rules have no legal force.

Sounds like good fun!   *8)

| favor |

