PROTO: Fix the @#!$%&* Speaker/Voter distinction

Amend Rule 103 to read as follows:

      At any time, each Player shall be either a Citizen or the Speaker;
      no Player may simultaneously be a Citizen and a Speaker. At any
      time, there shall be exactly one Speaker. The term "Player" in
      the Rules shall specifically include both the Citizens and the
      Speaker.

The Title of Rule 103 shall be Changed from "The Speaker and Voters" to
"The Speaker and the Citizens."

The following Rules are hereby amended by replacing each instance of the
word "Voter" with the word "Citizen" and by replacing each instance of
the word "Voters" with the word "Citizens":

    Rule 1043, Rule 1042, Rule  112, Rule  724, Rule 1433,Rule 785
    Rule  942, Rule  786, Rule  402, Rule 1427

Amend Rule 1498 by replacing the word "Player" with the word "Citizen"
and by deleting:

     , providing that Player has not also Won the previous Game in
     this manner

Amend Rule 1492 by replacing the first instance of the word "Player"
with the word "Citizen."



{Comment: I had to do this, since at least two othjer Players insisted it was
          too hienous an effort to eliminate this paticular Agoran
          archaism.  While this is AI=3 because of some of the high 
          precidence Rules involved, I would find controversy over this rather
          hard to understand.  The only changes in meaning here are in the
          new "Win" rules, where I reassert the original nomic idea that
          only someone other than the current Speaker should Win the Game--
          I can, however, drop the final two amendments if there are
          objections.  All else is simply changing a single confusing and
          now-erronious word.}

