The thought of virtual real estate (esp as a reward for something) sounded
intriguing to me... thus the proto:

<PROTO>
Protoproposal P000

Create a rule entitled "Position" with text:

        Every Nomic Entity has a Position, which is an ordered pair of
integers. If an entity's position is not defined elsewhere, it has the
default position of (0,0). Entities whose position is _defined_ to be (0,0)
elsewhere are not considered to have the default position.

        Agora Nomic has the position (0,0)

Create a rule entitled "Property" with text:

        Positions may be owned by a single Player, Organization, Nomic.
Other types of Entities, or groups of Entities, may only own Positions if
so allowed by the Rules. Positions may only be owned as described by the
Rules.

        Agora Nomic owns the position (0,0)

Create a rule entitled "The Realtor" with text:

        There exists the Office of the Realtor. The Realtor is responsible
for maintaining the position of all entities with non-default positions,
and ownership of positions. Once per week the Realtor shall post a Property
report, listing all non-default positions and owned positions, and changes
in such information since the previous report. The Realtor's salary is one
point per week.

Directive: Install Pascal as Realtor
</PROTO>

Not a very purposeful system yet...
I personally would find having a piece of property somewhere (with a
description or something I could set...) almost as satsfying as a Win...
especially if it was allowed for ex-players to own stuff, acting as kind of
a record.

sort of Pascal, (*7/6), (*8/6), (*9/6) .... (*13498984329239/6)
(as if _that_ would ever happen)
versus having a virtual statue of myself somewhere. or something.
*shrug*
---Pascal


