Wes Contreras sez:

> Well, we did request that Proposal submissions be sent to
> `nomic-props@magika.com', so perhaps this will be a good test of your
> theory. We hope to set up a script to assign numbers and mail
> notifications, but this won't work unless we can eliminate the
> possibility of other Proposals being sent to our normal mailbox. We have
> a feeling that other Offices could be simplified with the same process.

This is very interesting... :)

I am currently setting up a global database of Players, basically so 
that a) Scorekeepor eats up as little of my time as possible and b) I 
can have an idea of any Player's status at any time. Of course the 
time benefits of this are purely illusory since I will probably spend 
twice as much setting up my Perl programs than it would have taken me 
to record scores manually, but what the heck - it's the principle 
that counts. :)

I do intend to ultimately put these scripts and commands at the 
diposal of any Player, so that a majority of game actions can be 
automated - however, I will certainly *never* require as Scorekeepor 
that Players use these interfaces.

I suggest you do the same - if you get Proposals sent to your mailbox 
or the PF, set up your mailer to forward them to your scripts. There 
shouldn't be a danger of Agora becoming unplayable when some server 
goes down or whatever.

