So, let me paraphrase:

  Caller:  Statement:  X  
           Argument:   ..., for example Y

  Judge:   No, no, no.  X is TRUE.  But Y is not a correct example.
           Judgement:  FALSE.


This appears to take the all-time championship for shoddily-reasoned 
judgements, in a close field.  If I were still a player, I would not 
