- Agorasquare: 2n+1 x 2n+1, n initially at 3, coordinates from -n to +n
- All Players start at (0,0)
- n is increased once per 2 weeks (say) by 1
- This newly added space (8n+8 squares) contains n treasures: EV, Marks
and Point Caches in random locations, that can be won by entering the
square
- Moving around costs Marks, Points. Buying squares also on condition
that the Player is located there at the moment of the buy.
A square that is in possession of a Player, may not be entered
by another Player, unless a fee is paid
- Agora square contains Public Service squares like a Vote box, a Transfer
Office, a Post Office to mail discussion (now that will cut down the
mail traffic!)

Etc, etc.

Ronald

From nomic-discussion-owner@teleport.com  Thu Nov 30 06:05:47 1995
Received: from desiree.teleport.com (desiree.teleport.com [192.108.254.21]) by Shamino.quincy.edu (8.6.12/8.6.9) with ESMTP id GAA07367 for <blahedo@quincy.edu>; Thu, 30 Nov 1995 06:05:43 -0600
Received: (from daemon@localhost) by desiree.teleport.com (8.6.12/8.6.9) id PAA12755 for nomic-discussion-outgoing; Wed, 29 Nov 1995 15:45:47 -0800
Received: from Shamino.quincy.edu (blahedo@Shamino.quincy.edu [192.217.45.2]) by desiree.teleport.com (8.6.12/8.6.9) with ESMTP id PAA12618 for <nomic-discussion@teleport.com>; Wed, 29 Nov 1995 15:45:28 -0800
Received: (from blahedo@localhost) by Shamino.quincy.edu (8.6.12/8.6.9) id RAA30408 for nomic-discussion@teleport.com; Wed, 29 Nov 1995 17:46:14 -0600
From: Don Blaheta <blahedo@quincy.edu>
