X-mailer: Pegasus Mail for Windows (v2.20)
Sender: owner-nomic-business@teleport.com
Precedence: bulk
Reply-To: nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Status: RO

Proto-Proposal
---
Going On Strike

Create a Rule with the following text (Going On Strike)

   There exists a Strike whenever three or more Players send an 
   identical message to the Speaker mentioning the fact that these 
   Players are going On Strike and the name of every Player who is 
   doing so.  Such a message must also describe an Intolerable 
   Situation, defined as a condition or set of conditions that are 
   TRUE of the Game State at the time the message is sent.

   At any time that a Strike exists, additional Players may go On 
   Strike by sending a message to the Public Forum to that effect.

   Players who are On Strike may not take any action other than to 
   announce that they are going Off Strike, and are absolved from any 
   Duty that is required of them by the Rules. No Salaries, Bonuses
   or Awards are transferred to any Player who is On Strike, with 
   the exception of Blots.

   At the end of any full Nomic Week in which a Strike exists, all 
   Active Players except the Speaker and the CotC gain 1 Blot, which 
   gain is reported by the Speaker.

   If a CFJ to the effect that the Intolerabe Situation was not
   TRUE at the time the message is sent, or that there is no Move 
   or set of Moves that can be made such that the Intolerable 
   Situation becomes FALSE, the Strike ceases to exist and all 
   Players go Off Strike.

   Players who are On Strike are ineligible from Judging such a CJF.

   If at any time there are less that two Players On Strike, or the 
   Intolerable Situtation becomes FALSE, the Strike ceases to exist
   and all Players go Off Strike.

   The Speaker and CotC may not go On Strike.

   This Rule takes precedence over any Rule which would result in 
   this Rule not having effect.
---

Comments : I'll transfer 3 Marks to any Player (except Ronald) who 
first comes up with the reason why I'm posting this. :)

