Laurent Bossavit writes:
>
>Steve sez:
>
>> This is a highly inaccurate and misleading way of speaking about the
>> situation. One shouldn't toss the word 'paradox' about lightly.
>> Paradox is a serious matter.
>
>Maybe this is the right time to remind you that 'paradox' only means 
>'a statement that goes counter to accepted opinion'...

Actually, a paradox is a proposition whose truth implies its falsity,
and vice versa. Which is not quite what I said in the post (in a part
you didn't quote). There's a distinction between a paradox and
contradiction. Neither of them amount merely to being 'counter to
accepted opinion'.

