Here is a suite of Protos which is probably going to elicit LOTS of
comments. They're welcome, but try to keep them on the subject of how to
make the process better, not whether the process should be done or not.
At this point, it's a purely theoretical exercise; the decision about
whether or not to implement it will be made at some future date,
probably around Revision 15.0 or something... <grin> 


PROTO-PROPOSAL SUITE 
Self-Promoting/Assessing Proposals

-----
PROTO-PROPOSAL
Making and Distributing Proposals, Type II, Phase 1 

Amend Rule 1036 to read:

     Let there be an Officer called the Promotor. The Promotor shall
     receive a Weekly salary of 2 Points. A Proposal by a Player shall
     be made by sending it to the Promotor. As soon as possible after
     receiving the Proposal, the Promotor shall assign the Proposal a
     Number and notify the Player who submitted that Proposal of said
     Number. 

     Within seven days of receiving the Number of the Proposal, and
     prior to the posting of any Proposals subsequently submitted by
     that Player, the Player may post the Proposal to the Public 
     Forum, along with its Number and any comments the Player wishes to
     make. If the Player does not post the Proposal within seven days,
     or out of order, then that Proposal shall cease to be a valid
     Proposal and shall not be Voted upon or Adopted. 

[Phase 1 of the transferance is sort of a trial period without doing any
major surgery on the Rule Set, thus submissions to the Promotor are
still required to mesh with Rules 1061, 109, 659 and 1065. When those
Rules have been successfully Amended, then this can be further Amended
to Phase 2 and eliminate the Promotor entirely.] 

[The time limit and ordering requirement still remains because we can
see ways to abuse the system without such requirements, and it does not
seem to be too onerous. If the Player misses the "deadline", e has to
get a new Number and do it again.] 


History:
11/24: Proto 0.0 
-----
PROTO-PROPOSAL
New Assessor Salary

As the duties of the Assessor would be much less taxing, Amend Rule 1449
to replace the phrase:

     The Assessor has a weekly salary of 8 Points.

with: 

     The Assessor has a weekly salary of 3 Points. 


History:
11/24: Proto 0.0
-----
PROTO-PROPOSAL
Update Electioneering Rule

As the Assessor is no longer the one with confidential information, and
just to put the Rule straight with regards to any other Officer in the
future which might, Amend Rule 452 to read: 

     If any Player uses any knowledge of the current status of the Vote
     on a Proposal which e would not have known except for some official
     status, action, or recordkeeping in any attempt to influence the
     result of the Vote on that or any other Proposal, that Player shall
     be Guilty of a Class C Crime for each Proposal which e attempted to
     influence. 

     This Rule shall not apply to the posting of which Players have or
     have not Voted on a particular Proposal to tbe Public Forum. 

[General wording update which may be worth Proposing whether or not the
rest of the Suite is accepted. It still does everything the old Rule
does, but it also applies to other Officers and other Players who may be
dealing with confidential information, including Players Assessing their
own Proposals.] 


History:
11/24: Proto 0.0
-----
PROTO-PROPOSAL
Legal Votes, Type II, Phase 1

Amend Rule 683 to read:

{Rule Needs Work; Postponed for more Protos} 

-----
PROTO-PROPOSAL
End of the Voting Period, Type II, Phase 1 

Amend Rule 208 to read:

     As soon as possible after the end of the Voting Period on a given
     Proposal, the Player who Proposed that Proposal shall send all
     Votes which were legally cast to the Assessor. As soon as possible
     after receiving those Votes, the Assessor shall post them to the
     Public Forum. 

[This will fit in with Rules 312, 955, 376, 1443, 833, 1519, 947, 1047, 
1477, 1442, 1525, 1488, 1490, 1489, and Powers Rules. When these Rules have
been Amended, the Assessor can be eliminated from the process entirely.]

History:
11/24: Proto 0.0
-----



This should be a Phase 1 system which should get us about halfway to
having Players do their own work. LOTS of little adjustments will need
to be made to move the actual workload, however, before Phase 2 can be
completed. Of course, if it weren't for Rule 1065, this could all be done 
fairly quickly, but so be it.] 



Enjoy!

---
Promotor Wes
promotor@magika.com
Please submit all Proposals to `nomic-props@magika.com' 

