My personal aesthetic judgements tend to favor concepts broken into
simple modular rules that a) do one thing at a time (for the most part)
and b) use language as simply as possible.  I hade some of the twisted
sentance structure that gets into our Rules. (I've been as guilty of this as
anyone else, espcially when I use an old Rule as a template.)

