>> Wes>      An Entity is any thing which has definite, individual
>> Wes> existance.
>> 
>> hm.  so individual Marks, Points, etc are not Entities (since they
>> don't have "definite, individual existence", at least not in my
>> opinion).
>
><raise eyebrow> Oh, really? 

I think I see what Kelly is saying.  Suppose I have 9 Marks, and
Steve transfers 1 Mark to me.  I then transfer 1 Mark to you.
Is the Mark I transfered to you the same one that Steve transfered
to me, or is it one of the other nine?  That question cannot
be answered (by the current Rules), so Marks do not have an
individual existence.

Chuck

