I've watched the Agora Nomic list for a while; it seems you are having great
difficulty progressing on a definition of entity.  Why not resort to a simple
enumeration?

Anything not explicitly declared by the Rules to be an Entity is not an Entity.
Agora World is an Entity.
All Players are Entities.
All Points are Entities.
All Marks are Entities.
All Official Documents are Entities.

Just for clarification, you could list:
No Rules are Entities except via their inclusion in an Official Document.
No Salaries are Entities; however, the Points which result thereof are
Entities.

tim

