BTW, we just spotted a few things that put this argument to rest. 

"A Currency is a type of Nomic Entity" [Rule 1467/1]

"Any Entity which is created by the Nomic Rules... (such as Points,
Votes, Currencies and any Official Records)" [Rule 1011/0] 

"Offices are a class of Nomic Entities" [Rule 1006/4] 

In addition, Kudos, Patent Titles, Theses, the Potato, the Mint, 
and Indices are explicitly defined to be Entities, and Players and
Groups are indirectly defined to be Entities through their definition as
a Voting Entity. 

It would seem that Game Custom would bring a lot of weight into the
definition of an Entity. 


Enjoy!

