Precedence: bulk
Reply-To: nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Status: RO

I wish to request the Agorans' opinion of this. Is anyone very likely 
to vote AGAINST ?

Proto-Proposal
---
Short Rule Incentive

Create a rule with this text (Short Rule Incentive) :

   Any individual proposed Rule Change, with the exception of a
   Repeal, which as part or all of its effect, causes the affected 
   Medium or Long Rule to become Short, will cause the Player
   who proposed it to be awarded a bonus of two Points.

   Any individual proposed Rule Change which, as part or all of its
   effect, causes the affected Short or Medium Rule to become Long,
   will cause the Player who proposed it to be subject to a penalty
   of two Marks.

   The Rulekeepor is responsible for reporting these transfers as
   soon as possible after the Assessor reports the adoption of a
   Proposal containing such Rule Changes, and for determining the 
   Length of a Rule.

   The Rulekeepor shall report whenever e publishes the Ruleset what 
   criteria are used to determine the Length of a Rule. These criteria
   apply to all Rules and must be based only on the formatting of the 
   Rules. They can be changed only through the adoption of a 
   Directive to that effect.

Directive :

   The Rulekeepor is directed to report that a Short Rule is one
   under 10 lines in length when formatted to 70-column format,
   including a 6-space indent; that a Long Rule is one over 30 lines
   in length in that format; and that all other Rules are Medium.
---

Revision history :

1 - Oct. 30, original proto
2 - Oct. 31
No longer applies to all Rules, but only the changed Rule.
Specifies when the transfer takes effect.
3 - Nov. 5
Clears up how length is measured.
Repeals no longer count as 'short rules'.
4 - Dec. 5
Transferred responsibility for measuring and reporting to the 
Rulekeepor, to avoid problems with the manner of measuring
Rules.
No longer awards bonuses for amendments that don't change a
Rule's length.
Revised the relative importance of bonus/penalty.
5 - Dec. 5
Introduced Short, Medium and Long as 'variable' measurements for 
Rules. This way, the Ruleset format may still change after this is 
adopted.
6 - Dec. 6
The Formatting Directive now reflects Rulekeepor's Chuck format.

<Please don't quote this line -- PR-MORE-006>

-*-*-*-*-*-
 Morendil

