Proto-Proposal
(WAS : The Mutant)
---
Genetics (1 Creation, 1 Directive, 1 Repeal)

Create a Rule with this text (Genetics):

   There is a Rule known as The Mutant, and an integer known as
   the Number of the Beast. The Number of the Beast is determined
   by a Directive, and uniquely identifies The Mutant. If at any time 
   there is no Number of the Beast associated with an existing Rule, 
   this Rule has no effect.

   As soon as possible after the beginning of each Week, the 
   Rulekeepor shall select three random numbers :
    - P between 1 and 1000
    - N between 1 and 500
    - E between 1 and 100
   and an English language dictionary of eir choice. For the 
   purposes of this Rule, only those pages numbered with arabic
   numerals and containing dictionary entries are to be used.

   The Mutant shall then be modified in the manner of a non-Proposed
   Amendment by replacing the Nth word of The Mutant with the word
   corresponding to the Eth entry of page P of the selected dictionary,
   if and only if :
     - The Mutant contains N words or less;
     - the dictionary contains P pages or less
     - page P contains E entries or less;
     - the replacement does not result in a sentence that is 
       ungrammatical after properly conforming the replacement
       word to the grammatical attributes (tense, person, gender,
       number) of the word it replaces.

   The Rulekeepor shall publish the results of this process as soon 
   as possible after the beginning of any Nomic Week, but no sooner 
   than e actually applies it.

Directive : set the Number of the Beast to 1061.

Rule 1454 is Repealed.    
---

Comments : it should be much more interesting to see how a Rule 
Mutates than to simply Repeal it. This can be used as torture for 
Rules we dislike particularly. :)

