Ok, my finals ended a couple days ago, so I've taken advantage of the
incredible amount of free time to do a number of fun and interesting
Nomic-related things.

THE FIRST THING
The most important, probably, to everyone here, is the nomic-request
server.  Simply mail a message to me (blahedo@quincy.edu), with
"nomic-request" somewhere in the subject, and the server will process
your message.  It can serve up a number of files:
	* Proposals.  It can give _all_ the Proposals I have access
		to, not just the ones currently on the Web site.
	* CFJs.  It can serve any CFJ which I have, on the Web site or
		not.
	* Any files on the Web site.  Even if you don't have Web access,
		you can grab a file off the site.
The syntax is to type "get" as the first thing on a line (not including
whitespace), then type in all your requested files, separated by spaces.
To request Proposals, give P#### as the filename; to request CFJs, give
C#### as the filename, and to request web files, you'll have to look at
the index to see how I've named them all.

The other two commands besides "get" are "help" (which basically tells
you what I'm telling you now) and "index", which lists all the files you
can get.

Please, send me comments--I just wrote this last night/today, so it
probably still has a few bugs running around.


THE SECOND THING
The Notary is online!  At "http://www.quincy.edu/~blahedo/agora/notary/", 
I have a list of all Public Organizations, and their Administrators,
Executors, and Jurisdictions.  In addition, I have a copy of their
Compact, although it may not be quite up-to-date (but it _is_
Webbified.)  Administrators, if you update your Compact, please send me
a new copy, _and_ what changes were made--I will not rewebbify the
entire document, just the changed part.


THE THIRD THING
Remember a month ago when I asked everyone for some info about
themselves?  Well, I've been gleaning info from the servers since then,
and now, for your viewing pleasure, I am proud to present
"http://www.quincy.edu/~blahedo/bio.html", which contains Email
addresses for every player and active watcher, and a few ex-players;
homepages for people who have them; as much info as I could drag from
the Registrar's report about these people; and of course any
biographical info they've posted recently.  Check it out.  Once you've
checked it out, if you like, elect me as Registrar--I'd be happy to do
the work.


THE FOURTH AND FINAL THING
I have updated my Web pages in various places so that they refer to
relevant Rules on Chuck's page... perhaps minor, but it might be
convenient, and it may make it easier for newbies to "grasp the
concepts".

Vanyel

