Here is another fun batch of Proposals. Sorry for the delay in getting
them published. We're still getting used to the new Rule Set, and we
don't want to miss anything. 

----------

SUMMARY:

PROPOSAL 2046  (Chuck)     -  AI 1 
PROPOSAL 2047  (Kelly)     -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2048  (Morendil)  -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2049  (Vanyel)    -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2050  (Vanyel)    -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2051  (Vanyel)    -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2052  (Vanyel)    -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2053  (Vanyel)    -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2054  (Vanyel)    -  AI 1
PROPOSAL 2055  (Wes)       -  AI 1 
PROPOSAL 2056  (Wes)       -  AI 1

----------

BONUSES/PENALTIES:

Long Proposals - None 
Too Many Proposals - 
   Kelly loses 1 Mark for 2047 since it was submitted during the
     previous Nomic Week (last Sunday), even though it was distributed
     during this Nomic Week. 
   Vanyel loses 6 Marks for 2052, 2053, and 2054. 

Note: Everyone who submitted Proposals which have been Proto-Proposed
need to notify the *Assessor* of this fact prior to the conclusion of
the Voting Period for your Proposal. A comment attached to your Proposal
should do it, as long as you clearly mark it as intending it to be
distributed along with the Proposal. 

Also, Mr. Assessor, we Proto-Proposed both of our Proposals in this
batch. 

----------

PROPOSAL 2046  (Chuck)  -  AI 1 
Change Category of "Definition of Violations"

This Proposal contains zero proposed Rule Changes and one Directive.

I.  The Category of Rule 1538 shall be changed from "Definitions"
    to "Organizations."

[The most important part of my Proposal 1787, which narrowly failed.
Also, this is not included in Swann's Proposal 2027.  As I pointed
out before, the "Definitions" Category ought to be for *only* those
definitions which apply to many aspects of the game and do not
readily fit into any other Category (such as ASAP or Random).
The definition of Violation is not such a definition.]


[Distributed 12/9/95] 

----------

PROPOSAL 2047  (Kelly)  - AI 1
fix repeal bonuses

Be it therefore resolved, that Rule 947 be amended to read:

      If there are more than 100 Rules, and a Proposal is adopted
      which, as part or all of its effect, repeals one or more Rules,
      the Player who proposed that Proposal shall receive 5 Points.
      This transfer shall be reported by the Rulekeepor, who shall do
      so as soon as possible after the Proposal's Adoption.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

the Rulekeepor seems more appropriate to detect this condition, since
e is the one who actually applies the Rule Changes to the Ruleset.

also disinfects Rule 947.


[Submitted 12/3/95]
[Distributed 12/9/95] 

----------

PROPOSAL 2048  (Morendil)  -  AI 1
Update 1051

Amend Rule 1051 by replacing the second paragraph with :

   The Rulekeepor shall receive a weekly Salary of 5 Points.


[the Speaker *is* no longer required to maintain or publish 
the Ruleset unless Rulekeepor is vacant; also, the Rulekeepor *is* 
constrained by the Rules defining the Logical Ruleset.] 

[Submitted 12/5/95]
[Distributed 12/9/95]

----------

PROPOSAL 2049  (Vanyel)  -  AI 1
Fix tense in 1020

Whereas the tense of the verb in Rule 1020 is future (or declarative
mood, possibly),

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 1020 be Amended by replacing the
words "shall be" with "is".

[Comment: Protoed as Green-1.  Actually, it might not be future tense,
but at the very least it seems prescriptive as opposed to descriptive,
which I think should be reversed.]

[Submitted 12/5/95]
[Distrbuted 12/9/95] 

----------

PROPOSAL 2050  (Vanyel)  -  AI 1
Update and clarify 101

Whereas there is some outdated bootstrapping stuff in rule 101, and

Whereas Rule 101 currently implies some sort of Platonic ideal,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 101 be Amended by deleting the
following text:

      The Rules in the Initial Set are in effect at the beginning of the
      first game.  The Initial Set consists of Rules 101-116 (Immutable)
      and 201-219 (Mutable).

[Comment: Protoed as Green-2]

[Submitted 12/5/95]
[Distrbuted 12/9/95] 

----------

PROPOSAL 2051  (Vanyel)  -  AI 1
Clarify Permissibility vs. Possibility

Whereas various Players have misinterpreted Rule 116 as granting
possibility to certain impossible actions,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 116 is Amended by appending the
following text:

      However, the permissibility of an Action in no way indicates the
      possibility of that Action.

[Comment: Vacuous it may be, but I think it is an important
clarification.  The voters will decide.  Protoed as Green-3.]

[Submitted 12/5/95]
[Distributed 12/9/95] 

----------

PROPOSAL 2052  (Vanyel)  -  AI 1
The PF is your own problem

Whereas the Distributor no longer directly sends out Official
messages, and

Whereas the Distributor does not have absolute control over the
subscription lists of the Public Forum listservers,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 478 be Amended by replacing the
text

      Subscription may be necessary to be able to receive the Public
      Forum, in which case such a subscription is mandatory to all
      Players.

with

      It is the Player's responsibility to receive all media which
      comprise the Public Forum.

Be it further resolved that the word "send" be changed to "sent".

[Comment: A necessary change, I think.  Protoed as Green-5.
Incidentally, an insane distributor wouldn't matter here, because
any message to all Players is ok for PF stuff.]

[Submitted 12/5/95]
[Distributed 12/9/95]

----------

PROPOSAL 2053  (Vanyel)  -  AI 1
Un-mathify Indices

Whereas the second paragraph of Rule 1274 is somewhat difficult to
read,

Be it therefore resolved that the second and final paragraph of Rule
1274 be Amended to read as follows:

      An Index of Unanimity is greater than any other Index.  When
      comparing other Indices, the Index which is numerically greater is
      the greater Index.

[Comment: Protoed as Green-7.]

[Submitted 12/5/95]
[Distrbuted 12/9/95]

----------

PROPOSAL 2054  (Vanyel)  -  AI 1
Who wants to discourage Proposals?

Whereas the current 1065 is too restrictive,

Be it therefore resolved that Rule 1065 be Amended by replacing "two" in
the first paragraph with "five".

[Comment: Not protoed.]

[Submitted 12/5/95]
[Distributed 12/9/95]

----------

PROPOSAL 2055  (Wes)  -  AI 1 

Amend Rule 1538 to read:  

     Any Player who fails to comply with the Rules has Violated the
     Rules. Any Player who fails to comply with a Compact while within
     that Compact's Jurisdiction has Violated that Compact. 

     Any Violation of a Rule is a Rules Violation. Any Violation of a 
     Compact which results in a Violation to the Rules is a Rules Violation. 
     Any Violation of a Compact which does not result in a Rules Violation 
     is a Civil Violation. 

Amend Rule 1529 by appending the following text to the paragraph which 
begins "i) Statutes": 

     Any Violation of a Statute is also a Violation of this Rule. 


[Submitted 12/9/95]
[Distributed 12/9/95]

----------

PROPOSAL 2056  (Wes)  -  AI 1
Legislating custom

Amend Rule 1036 to replace the text:

     the Promotor shall distribute the numbered Proposal to all Players

with the text:

     the Promotor shall post the Proposal to the Public Forum
     accompanied by its Number, the name of the Player who Proposed the
     Proposal, and its Adoption Index


[It seems as though these requirements are not legislated anywhere at
this time.]

[Submitted 12/9/95]
[Distributed 12/9/95]

----------


Enjoy!

