Sender: owner-nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Precedence: bulk
Reply-To: nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Status: O

> Runs into trouble from the opposite direction: email addresses are
> properties referred to the by the Rules which may be changed despite
> the Rules being utterly silent on how this happens.

Perhaps we need the concept of "Rigorously Defined Entity". A RDE may *only* be
changed as defined in Agora Rules, whereas other entities may *conceivably* be
changed by other means. For example, a Point will be a RDE, but an email
address is not.

Then, once we change Rule 1011 to define "Rigorously Defined Entity", we need
to massively amend the Rule Set to specify which Entities are Rigorously
Defined. There would be many such Entities which are Rigorous, thus many
amendments. But perhaps this must be done.

All the suggesions up to now have failed to provide an unambiguous means of
distinguishing between Entities which can change outside of the Rules and which
cannot. There may be no good way other than to explicitely define which ones
cannot. 


-- KoJen

