David Cogen was heard to say:
> 
>All the suggesions up to now have failed to provide an unambiguous means of
>distinguishing between Entities which can change outside of the Rules and which
>cannot. There may be no good way other than to explicitely define which ones
>cannot. 

Does anyone besides Kelly object to the following Proto on any grounds?


PROTO-PROPOSAL  (Wes) 
Definition of Entities

Amend Rule 1011 to read: 

     An Entity is any thing which has definite, individual existance. A
     Nomic Entity is any Entity which exists within the context of Agora
     Nomic. A Game Entity is any Nomic Entity which exists solely within
     the context of Agora Nomic. 
     
     No Game Entity may be changed except as specified within the Rules.
     No two Nomic Entities shall share the same Name or official
     Nickname. 


11/24: Proto 0.0
11/26: Proto 1.0 
12/01: Repost 1.0 



Enjoy!

