> Runs into trouble from the opposite direction: email addresses are
> properties referred to the by the Rules which may be changed despite
> the Rules being utterly silent on how this happens.

So you're saying that it's okay to make things illegal which will happen
anyways? In the beginning Agora Nomic, that sort of Rule would be
considered a Paradox and would end the Game, giving a Win to whoever
pointed it out. 




