"Wes" == Wes Contreras <magika@teleport.com> writes:

Wes> We are attempting to show that a Mark can be an Entity in spite
Wes> of the fact that it can be broken into pieces by attempting to
Wes> show that the word entity can refer to a collection of similar or
Wes> related items rather than solely to the component parts which
Wes> make up that set.

if this is what you are doing, then you have changed your argument
since this particular discussion started.  this discussion began when
it was suggested that Entities could be characterized as having
"distinct, individual" existence, and i rebutted that Marks (and other
Currencies) do not appear to have "distinct, individual" existence.  i
do not deny that Marks (or, more properly, centimarks) are Entities; i
deny that they have distinct, individual existence, and is it this
point that i have been arguing.  

kindly refrain from strawmanning my arguments.

k.
