>If I may be so bold, may I suggest we call these "the Smaragdine
>Repeals" since they are essentially a re-proposal of the Green
>Repeals. :)

They're the Green Repeals with a twist: all of them are AI=1, even
those that can repeal AI>1 Rules.  (The Rule that should prevent that,
recently discussed, is only AI=1, and now actually explicitly defers to
the Rules these Proposals would create.)  I think whatever name we come
up with should reflect that fact.

Oh, yeah, everyone who wanted to repeal 101, here's your
once-in-a-lifetime chance to do it by convincing a simple majority of
the Players.  That is, unless you're chicken...

Stats: of the 230 Proposals, I have voted FOR 142 and AGAINST the other
88.

As everyone has had all the time since the Green Repeals to think about
whether each Rule is really necessary, lack of time to consider each
Proposal individually is now no excuse for a blanket vote.  I may well
deKudo anyone that does a blanket vote of FOR or AGAINST.

-zefram

