Sender: owner-nomic-business@teleport.com
Precedence: bulk
Reply-To: nomic-discussion@teleport.com
Status: O

Proto-Proposal
---
Respawning

Create a Rule with this text (Respawning) :

   Any Rule may specify that it respawns itself. This shall be a 
   clear and unambiguous way of referring to the process whereby, an 
   infinitesimal amount of time before any Rule Change which Repeals 
   such a Rule takes effect, the affected Rule creates, in the manner of a 
   non-Proposed Rule Change, a new Rule with the exact text of the 
   Repealed Rule, and further that, an infinitesimal amount of time 
   after such a Repeal takes effect, the newly-created Rule changes 
   its own Rule Number to that of the most recently Repealed Rule. 
   These amounts of time shall be smaller than any other amount of 
   time referred to in other Rules.

   If a Proposal contains both an amendment to an existing Rule and 
   the Repeal of a Rule with the same Rule Number, the Repeal shall 
   take effect first if the Proposal is adopted; this takes precedence
   over any Rule specifying a different ordering for the effects of a 
   Proposal.

   This Rule respawns itself.
---

Comments : my attempt at 'elite' Rules. This lets us have a way 
of specifically protecting some Rules against blanket Repeals. Note 
that Repeals in general, and even blanket Repeals, remain feasible, 
but require two Proposals instead of one; the first to amend 
respawning out of the Rule, the second to actually Repeal the Rule.

Revision history:
1 - Dec. 15, original proto

