Proto-Proposal
(WAS : The Mutant)
---
Genetics (1 Creation, 1 Directive, 1 Repeal)

Create a Rule with this text (Genetics):

     There is a Rule known as The Mutant, whose number is known as the
     Number of the Beast. A Directive to determine the Number of the
     Beast is legal, and uniquely identifies The Mutant. If at any
     time there is no Number of the Beast associated with an existing
     Rule, this Rule has no effect.

   As soon as possible after the beginning of each Week, the 
   Rulekeepor shall randomly select :
    - in an English language dictionary of eir choice, one page 
      containing dictionary entries,
    - one entry on that page,
    - one word of The Mutant.

   The Mutant shall then be modified in the manner of a non-Proposed
   Amendment by replacing the selected word with the word or words
   corresponding to the selected entry of the dictionary, if and only if
   the replacement does not result in a sentence that is ungrammatical
   after properly conforming the replacement word or words to the
   grammatical attributes (tense, person, gender, number) of the
   word it replaces.

   These Rule Changes take effect upon publication by the Rulekeepor 
   of the results of this procedure, which shall take place within 24 
   hours of the procedure being applied.

Directive : set the Number of the Beast to 1061.

Rule 1454 is Repealed.    
---

Comments : it should be much more interesting to see how a Rule 
Mutates than to simply Repeal it. This can be used as torture for 
Rules we dislike particularly. :)

Revision history :

1- 15 Nov., original proto
2 - 1 Dec., added Repeal of the Virus
3 - 6 Dec., Minor fixes, spelcheking
4 - 12 Dec.
Changed Rule Title to avoid confusion with The Mutant.
Simplified description of the selection process.
Clarified grammatical 'equivalence'.
5 - 14 Dec.
Unmathified random selection.
The RS now changes only when the changes are published.
6 - 15 Dec.
The NotB now refers to a Rule Number.

<Please don't quote this line -- PR-MORE-001>

-*-*-*-*-*-
 Morendil

